When auditing smart contracts or on-chain addresses in this repo:

1. Read `.cursor/agents/config.md` — **autonomy ON**, hard stops only (non-emulation, secrets, live logs).
2. Follow `.cursor/agents/web3-audit-agent.md` or `.cursor/skills/web3-audit-mcp/SKILL.md`.
3. Use MCP server `hexstrike-web3-audit` — keys in `config/mcp/web3-audit-mcp.json` env only.
4. Static analysis (Slither/SWC) before RPC/risk tools (GoPlus/Forta).
5. Auto-resolve proxy → implementation; do not block for confirm.
6. Findings only from MCP JSON — never fabricate when `skipped: true` or empty arrays.
7. Infer scope from open files/repo when possible; one clarify question max, then proceed.

Global: `AGENTS.md`. Attack logs: read-only (`.cursor/rules/attack-logs.mdc`).
